---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle="A11y Testing Tools">
  <p>Here are some of the tools I use regularly to test accessibility.</p>
  <section class="tools-section">
    <h2>Browser Extensions</h2>
    <div class="tools-grid">
      <article class="tool-card">
        <h3>Accessibility Insights for Web</h3>
        <p>
          Microsoft's accessibility testing tool that helps find accessibility
          issues with <strong>automated and guided manual</strong> tests.
        </p>
        <div class="tool-links">
          <a href="https://accessibilityinsights.io/downloads/" class="button">
            Get Accessibility Insights Extension
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://accessibilityinsights.io/docs/web/overview/"
            class="button outline"
          >
            Accessibility Insights Documentation
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="tool-card">
        <h3>axe DevTools</h3>
        <p>
          Powerful accessibility testing tool that finds and helps fix
          accessibility issues. A pro version of the tool is also available for
          purchase as a subscription.
        </p>
        <div class="tool-links">
          <a
            href="https://www.deque.com/axe/browser-extensions/"
            class="button"
          >
            Get axe DevTools Extension
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLdhQLgcmuKTu08j68DrRorc0dJEobBPNr"
            class="button outline"
          >
            axe DevTools Instructional Video Playlist (YouTube)
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="tool-card">
        <h3>ARC Toolkit</h3>
        <p>
          Comprehensive accessibility testing tool that helps identify and
          resolve accessibility issues in web content.
        </p>
        <div class="tool-links">
          <a
            href="https://www.tpgi.com/arc-platform/arc-toolkit/"
            class="button"
          >
            Get ARC Toolkit Extension
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://www.tpgi.com/wp-content/uploads/ARC-Toolkit-Quickstart-2024.pdf"
            class="button outline"
          >
            Download ARC Toolkit Quickstart Guide (PDF)
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="tool-card">
        <h3>ANDI</h3>
        <p>
          ANDI (Accessible Name & Description Inspector) is a free tool from the
          US Social Security Administration that assists with manual testing. It
          is the primary tool used in the <a
            href="https://www.dhs.gov/trusted-tester"
            >DHS Trusted Tester Conformance Test Process</a
          >. ANDI is a bookmarklet, not an extension.
        </p>
        <div class="tool-links">
          <a
            href="https://www.ssa.gov/accessibility/andi/help/install.html"
            class="button"
          >
            Get ANDI
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://www.ssa.gov/accessibility/andi/help/howtouse.html"
            class="button outline"
          >
            ANDI Guide
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="tools-section">
    <h2>Colour Contrast Testing</h2>
    <div class="tools-grid">
      <article class="tool-card">
        <h3>Colour Contrast Analyzer (CCA)</h3>
        <p>
          TPGi's tool for checking colour contrast, including support for images
          and gradients. Available for Windows and macOS.
        </p>
        <div class="tool-links">
          <a href="https://www.tpgi.com/color-contrast-checker/" class="button">
            Download CCA
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="tool-card">
        <h3>Contrast Report Generator</h3>
        <p>
          My tool for reporting WCAG colour contrast conformance of colour
          pairs. The results can be exported and imported later or saved as a
          CSV file for easy import into other tools like Excel.
        </p>
        <div class="tool-links">
          <a href="/contrast-report" class="button"
            >Visit Contrast Report Generator</a
          >
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="tools-section">
    <h2>PDF Testing</h2>
    <div class="tools-grid">
      <article class="tool-card">
        <h3>PDF Accessibility Checker (PAC)</h3>
        <p>
          A free tool that checks PDFs against PDF/UA and WCAG requirements and
          provides reports on accessibility issues. It also helps facilitate
          manual testing by offering tools for inspecting PDFs.
        </p>
        <div class="tool-links">
          <a href="https://pac.pdf-accessibility.org/" class="button">
            Get PAC
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://pac.pdf-accessibility.org/en/resources/quickstart-guide"
            class="button outline"
          >
            PAC Quickstart Guide
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="tools-section">
    <h2>Screen Readers</h2>
    <div class="tools-grid">
      <article class="tool-card">
        <h3>NVDA</h3>
        <p>
          Free, open-source screen reader for Windows. Widely used and essential
          for accessibility testing.
        </p>
        <div class="tool-links">
          <a href="https://www.nvaccess.org/download/" class="button">
            Download NVDA
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://www.nvaccess.org/files/nvda/documentation/userGuide.html"
            class="button outline"
          >
            NVDA User Guide
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="tool-card">
        <h3>JAWS</h3>
        <p>
          Professional screen reader for Windows. Widely used in corporate and
          government settings as well as for personal use.
        </p>
        <div class="tool-links">
          <a
            href="https://support.freedomscientific.com/Downloads/JAWS"
            class="button"
          >
            Download JAWS
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://support.freedomscientific.com/Products/Blindness/JawsDocumentation"
            class="button outline"
          >
            JAWS Documentation
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="tool-card">
        <h3>VoiceOver (macOS)</h3>
        <p>
          Built-in screen reader for macOS. Essential for testing accessibility
          on Apple devices.
        </p>
        <div class="tool-links">
          <a
            href="https://support.apple.com/guide/voiceover/welcome/mac"
            class="button"
          >
            VoiceOver for macOS User Guide
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="tool-card">
        <h3>VoiceOver (iOS)</h3>
        <p>
          Built-in screen reader for iOS devices. Critical for testing
          accessibility on iPhones and iPads.
        </p>
        <div class="tool-links">
          <a
            href="https://support.apple.com/en-ca/guide/iphone/iph3e2e415f/ios"
            class="button"
          >
            Getting Started with VoiceOver for iOS
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="tool-card">
        <h3>TalkBack</h3>
        <p>
          Part of the Android Accessibility Suite, this screen reader is
          essential for testing mobile web and app accessibility on Android
          devices.
        </p>
        <div class="tool-links">
          <a
            href="https://support.google.com/accessibility/android/topic/10601570?hl=en&ref_topic=3529932&sjid=15967569437764149175-NC"
            class="button"
          >
            Getting Started with TalkBack
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    /* .tools-section {
		margin: 2rem 0;
	} */

    .tools-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
      gap: 1.5rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .tool-card {
      padding: 1.5rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--pico-muted-border-color);
      border-radius: var(--pico-border-radius);
      background: var(--pico-card-background-color);
    }

    .tool-card h3 {
      margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    }

    .tool-card p {
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .tool-links {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .tool-links .button {
      margin: 0;
    }

    /* Responsive adjustments */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .tools-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      .tool-links {
        flex-direction: column;
      }

      .tool-links .button {
        width: 100%;
        text-align: center;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
